actors.biography: Leonardo DiCaprio is an American actor and environmental activist, known for his intense roles and dedication to his craft. Born in Los Angeles on November 11, 1974, DiCaprio has been a prominent figure in Hollywood for decades. He gained widespread fame with roles in films such as 'Titanic' and 'Inception,' and won his first Academy Award for Best Actor for his performance in 'The Revenant.' Beyond acting, DiCaprio is known for his environmental advocacy and philanthropic work.

actors.biography: Tom Hanks is an American actor, director, and producer, known for his iconic roles in both comedic and dramatic films. Born on July 9, 1956, in Concord, California, Hanks became one of Hollywood's most beloved stars with roles in films like 'Forrest Gump,' 'Cast Away,' and 'Saving Private Ryan.' He has won multiple awards, including two Academy Awards for Best Actor for 'Forrest Gump' and 'Philadelphia.' Hanks is known for his versatility, charisma, and relatable on-screen presence.

actors.biography: Meryl Streep is an American actress widely regarded as one of the greatest performers in the history of cinema. Born on June 22, 1949, in Summit, New Jersey, Streep has received numerous accolades for her work, including three Academy Awards and a record 21 nominations. Known for her exceptional ability to portray diverse characters, her standout films include 'Sophie's Choice,' 'The Devil Wears Prada,' and 'Kramer vs. Kramer.' Streep's remarkable versatility has made her a beloved figure in both dramatic and comedic roles.

actors.biography: Matthew McConaughey is an American actor, producer, and director, known for his versatile roles in both dramatic and comedic films. He was born on November 4, 1969, in Uvalde, Texas, USA. McConaughey gained fame with his breakthrough role in the 1993 film 'Dazed and Confused.' Over the years, he became a household name with roles in films such as 'The Lincoln Lawyer,' 'Interstellar,' and 'Dallas Buyers Club,' the latter of which earned him an Academy Award for Best Actor. McConaughey has also ventured into writing and directing, with his memoir 'Greenlights' becoming a bestseller. His charismatic personality and 'Texas charm' have made him a beloved figure both on and off the screen.

actors.biography: Brad Pitt is an American actor and film producer, one of the most well-known and bankable stars in Hollywood. Born on December 18, 1963, in Shawnee, Oklahoma, Pitt gained international fame with roles in films like 'Fight Club,' 'Inglourious Basterds,' and 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood.' Pitt is also a successful producer and co-founded the production company Plan B Entertainment.

actors.biography: Emma Stone is an American actress known for her roles in both comedic and dramatic films. actors.biography: Chris Hemsworth is an Australian actor known for his role as Thor in the Marvel Cinematic Universe.
